The White House has announced that Elizabeth Sherwood-Randall will be moving to a new position as the White House Coordinator for Defense Policy, Countering Weapons of Mass Destruction, and Arms Control. Sherwood-Randall, who currently serves as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for European Affairs, will begin her new role on April 8. National Security Advisor Tom Donilon praised her leadership and expertise in defense issues and proliferation prevention. Sherwood-Randall has previously held positions in the Clinton Administration, as well as at Harvard University, Stanford University, the Council on Foreign Relations, and the Brookings Institution.